{"questionId":"14619698","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, or otherwise, find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>'</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>.</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>'</mo></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>B</mi></math></p>\n<p>(region/value may be seen in a correctly shaded/labeled Venn diagram)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: For the final mark, 0.2 must be stated as the candidate’s answer, or labeled as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>'</mo></mrow></mfenced></math> in their Venn diagram. Just seeing an unlabeled 0.2 in the correct region of their diagram earns <em><strong>M1A0</strong></em>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14619698","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ1.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, or otherwise, find PA'∩B'.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—St